"{\"uid\": \"worldathletics.org-news-report-kejelcha-ethiopia-olympic-10000m-trials-nerja\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Yomif Kejelcha wins the 10,000m in Nerja(\\u00a9Sportmedia)  Yomif Kejelcha took a thrilling narrow win at the Ethiopian 10,000m Olympic trials held on Friday (14) night in Nerja, Spain.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yomif Kejelcha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\"}, {\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nerja\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\"}, {\"begin\": 55, \"end\": 69, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yomif Kejelcha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\"}, {\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9809976785528248, \"rank\": 0.01937040408514573, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 167, \"end\": 172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nerja\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\"}, {\"begin\": 174, \"end\": 179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9051310588735682, \"rank\": 0.10480931589596473, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 26-year-old smashed his lifetime best by 18 seconds to clock a world-leading 26:31.01 after an incredibly tight sprint with Berihu Aregawi, who also improved his career best to 26:31.13.\", \"from\": 182, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berihu Aregawi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The third spot on Ethiopia's team for Paris went to Olympic champion Selemon Barega, who was timed at 26:34.93.\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 391, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999813554, \"rank\": 1.8520218947360405e-11, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 411, \"end\": 416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999853284873, \"rank\": 1.467151782781071e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selemon_Barega\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Selemon Barega\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selemon_Barega\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selemon_Barega\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of the highest quality 10,000m races ever, four men finished inside 26:40 and six men finished inside 26:50 for the first time.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"17-year-old Biniam Mehary placed fourth in a world U20 record of 26:37.93, taking four seconds off the previous mark set 19 years ago by the late Samuel Wanjiru.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9501466760159055e-19, \"text\": \"U20\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 774, \"end\": 781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Wanjiru\", \"score\": 0.9999999883518741, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wanjiru\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Wanjiru\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Wanjiru\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On an mild (21C) windless night and in a race with good pacemaking, Aregawi, Kejelcha, Barega and Mehari went through the halfway mark in 13:17.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"score\": 0.9810060459411328, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mehari\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One kilometre later, the last pacemaker dropped out of the race and from then on the world 5km record-holder Aregawi pushed hard, trying to leave his rivals behind, but only the young Mehari lost ground in the ninth kilometre.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"score\": 0.9810060459411328, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mehari\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortly after reaching the bell, Barega began to fade and the event became a two-way showdown between Aregawi and Kejelcha.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter tried to overtake his compatriot on the final bend, but Aregawi managed to hold off his first attack; Kejelcha never surrendered and finally he edged ahead of Aregawi just 30 metres before the finish line.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's race, Fotyen Tesfay took an impressive victory in 29:47.71, putting her just outside the top 10 on the world all-time list.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2023 world cross-country silver medallist Tsigie Gebreselama was second in 29:49:33, ahead of world bronze medallist Ejgayehu Taye (29:50:52), who also set a lifetime best.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsigie_Gebreselama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tsigie Gebreselama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsigie_Gebreselama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsigie_Gebreselama\"}, {\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ejgayehu_Taye\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ejgayehu Taye\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ejgayehu_Taye\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ejgayehu_Taye\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emeterio Valiente for World Athletics\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doreen_Valiente\", \"score\": 0.9999999999329248, \"rank\": 6.089424880443497e-11, \"text\": \"Valiente\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doreen_Valiente\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doreen_Valiente\"}]}]}"